Ad Text:
StewartBrown 
 

StewartBrown, Chartered Accountants, was established in 1939 and is one of Australia’s oldest independent professional firms, renowned for its trusted service and ethical reputation.

Recognised as the lead accounting firm for the Australian care sector, StewartBrown provide Consulting, Audit, Business Services, Taxation and Financial Benchmarking services to a national network of clients, delivered by a growing team of talented professionals dedicated to helping clients achieve their financial goals.

 With a particular focus on the not-for-profit sector, we work with a diverse range of businesses, organisations and entities across aged, community and disability care, health and children’s services and charities in addition to independent schools, licensed clubs and the broader commercial sector.

Our team of collaborative Consulting team members are committed to making a difference through work that delivers meaningful support and drives positive change. Our dynamic and supportive workplace culture reflects our core values of integrity, quality, and clarity and our absolute commitment to always putting our clients first to meet their professional needs.

The Opportunity 

StewartBrown is looking for a Senior Business Analyst to join our Consulting Team and your role may include:

Building and developing financial models, performing analysis, and presenting findings for clients

Conducting data analysis, reconciliations, and reporting to generate strategic insights.

Applying professional skepticism to ensure data integrity and accuracy in financial and operational analysis.

Communicating with clients and stakeholders throughout project lifecycles · Supporting project delivery, collaborating closely with senior leadership and clients

Driving the use of AI technologies to improve efficiency in analysis, forecasting, and reporting, embedding automation and intelligence into business processes.

What you can offer StewartBrown 

The ideal candidate will have; 

Tertiary qualifications with degree in Accounting, Business Analytics or related

A thorough understanding of database techniques and how to interpret information

5+ years of experience in financial or data analysis, consulting, statistics, or a related field

Advanced Excel, Word, PowerPoint & BI skills

AI and machine learning experience to identify patterns, forecast trends, and support data-driven strategic recommendations.

Exceptional attention to detail and analytical capabilities · Strong written and oral communications skills

Strong organisational skills

Team oriented

An ability to interact with stakeholders to provide timely responses and feedback

A commitment to quality improvement and best practice

Australian citizenship or residency or legal working entitlements within Australia.

Desirable: 

Experience in Consulting, statistics, or a related field highly regarded

Experience in preparing and reviewing financial and management information for decision making

Understanding of the NDIS, Aged Care and/or other Not-for-Profit Sectors

 What StewartBrown can offer you 

At StewartBrown we truly value our people. We are committed to offering more than just a job; we offer benefits and flexibility to enhance your work life, help you grow, and celebrate your achievements. These benefits include: 

Above award remuneration

Tailored employee support initiatives such as Wellness Leave; up to 5 extra days of leave a year to support balance, wellness, and overall health

Training and development opportunities 

Career progression opportunities 

Team sporting and social activities

We value diversity and welcome people from a range of backgrounds and experiences. If you are interested in applying for this opportunity and believe you have the required skills and experience, upload your application and cover letter.

If you are interested in applying for this opportunity and believe you have the required skills and experience, APPLY NOW!  

We appreciate everyone who has taken the time to apply but only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

About Cbus

Created by workers, for workers, Cbus Super is one of Australia’s most successful Superannuation funds. For four decades we’ve proudly represented those who help shape Australia, hard-working individuals who deserve to make the most of their retirement, no matter the industry. As an award-winning fund we’ve been recognised for the benefits provided to our members and our innovative investment approach.  All while staying committed to our member first ethos as a proud Industry Fund.

About the role

You will lead the strategic oversight and continuous improvement of Cbus’ enterprise risk system, Archer, and enable data-driven decision-making across the organisation.

This will include:

Ensuring our Enterprise Risk Management platform supports effective risk identification, assessment, monitoring, and reporting.
Ensuring data integrity, governance, and analytical capabilities meet internal and external requirements.
Lead training, communications, and change management initiatives to embed the usage of Archer, ensuring it is the source of truth for risk data.
Identify opportunities to enhance risk data analytics, automation, and dashboarding
Provide direct support to the Group Head of Enterprise Risk and Compliance and the Chief Risk Officer.
 
Experience and Qualifications

You’ll bring:  

Extensive experience in enterprise governance,risk management, or incident management, within financial services or a regulated industry.
Experience working with regulatory frameworks and standards (e.g., CPS 230, CPS 234).
Proven leadership in system implementation, stakeholder engagement, and change management.
Demonstrated ability to translate strategic priorities into operational reality, through delegation, managing team performance, creating accountability, and aligning systems and processes
Ability to identify opportunities for change and influence change and lead continuous improvement initiatives
  
Key to your success will be your ability to develop and leverage strong relationships at all levels, both internally and externally.   You will lead the consolidation of a critical platform which supports our Risk practice both now and into the future. 

Belong at Cbus
We value difference, and embrace people with diverse backgrounds, experiences, gender identities, abilities and thinking styles. We believe that, with diversity of perspectives and experiences, you get better teams and outcomes. We’re looking for people of all genders, races, nationalities, orientations and of all abilities to join us.
  
We’re keen to hear from you
If you've read through the requirements of this role and you feel like you haven’t fully met the criteria, we would still encourage you to apply. We're aware of accessibility barriers when it comes to applying for a job and we want to help.
If you require assistance with your application, please contact our Talent Acquisition Team via careers@cbussuper.com.au 

Like to know more about working with Cbus? Listen to some of our videos with members of the Cbus team on our website, cbussuper.com.au/careers
  
Applications Close:  Friday, 28th November  

This is a full-time position based in Melbourne. 
  
Agencies, please note: All Cbus vacancies are managed by our internal Talent Acquisition Team.  Should external assistance be required we will reach out to our preferred agency partners, thank you.

Commercially savvy? Client centric?  Focussed on growth?  Join our award-winning agency!

ABOUT US

TRA is an insights agency intent on solving complex business problems. We put people back at the heart of the organisations we work with, and in doing so help them foster success and see the opportunities for growth.

We are growing and looking for ambitious, curious and growth orientated Business Director to join our Sydney team.

With a strong quantitative research background, you will work alongside Australia’s top organisations solving problems and enabling decision making. You will be a critical leader in our growing business, with voice and influence in the direction we take into the future, working alongside like-minded, passionate researchers and a really connected, high performing team culture.

ABOUT THE ROLE

Seen as a trusted partner, this exciting opportunity will see you play the leading role in driving new business growth, excellence in relationship management and talent development. 

You will be responsible for key client relationships, understanding and exploring their businesses objectives, and working with them and our team to design and deliver solutions that enables decision making and unlocks growth. 
 
Taking an active role in both finding and delivering amazing work, you will be a leader in a growing agency with great momentum, responsible for nurturing success for both clients and the internal team.  

With significant experience in the quantitative practice, you will play a trusted advisor across a breadth of quantitative work, including brand tracking, for clients and our growing quantitative researchers.



Requirements



ABOUT YOU 

We are looking for someone who:  

Is passionate about joining a growth minded, deeply collaborative organisation 
Is comfortable talking to a wide variety of specialities such as qual, quant, culture, strategy, and behaviour change – to supplement their quantitative craft  
Has an excellent knowledge of insights covering a range of project areas, including tracking, usage and attitude studies, brand and communication development and testing, innovation and NPD  
Develops deep understandings of the businesses you work with.  
Builds long lasting relationships that deliver the best value to both parties.  
Feels at home both behind the tools and in the boardroom.  
Innovatively and creatively find solutions and is open to new ideas.  
Desires to encourage, train and develop others and share knowledge / expertise company wide.  


Benefits



WHY WORK HERE

Join an award-winning agency that values innovation and transformative thinking. TRA has been named Research Agency of the Year, AU/NZ, B&T Awards 2024  

TRA has also been awarded AFR BOSS Most Innovative Company, Professional Services (2024), Gold for Campaign Asia-Pacific Market Research Agency of the Year and Silver for Independent Agency of the Year, in Australia and New Zealand in 2023, and most recently won  Global Gold at the 2025 @ESOMAR Awards for Excellence in Global Research. 

Do the best work of your life, alongside some of the greatest thinkers you’ll encounter in your career and be part of the formative TRA Sydney team as we continue to grow our footprint. Our senior leaders will be working hands on alongside you, with opportunity to learn, grow and develop while doing incredibly valuable work.  
 
You’ll be working in a dynamic, new, modern office in Surry Hills – inspired and connected into creative, strategic people and businesses. We are a curious, creative, and multi-disciplinary team committed to delivering amazing work built on values of collaboration, creativity, and clarity.  
 
We have regular social events, some flexibility to work from home, and a competitive salary package to underpin the experience!   

 
WE VALUE DIVERSITY IN ALL ITS FORMS
We welcome applications from people of all backgrounds. We know from research that women or non-binary applicants don’t always apply for roles they don’t feel 100% qualified for, so we encourage anyone who is interested to get in touch. Focus on the bullet points that match your experience, not the ones that don’t.

Our job posting is the starting point for a conversation, and we’re always excited to hear from people who are interested in working with us.

If you’re curious, apply now! We’d love to hear from you.

Role: Senior SAP SuccessFactors Analyst
Day Rate: $800 - $1000 + Super
Contract Length: 6-months (likely extensions)
Location: Parramatta/WFH Hybrid

Join a high-performing HR technology team supporting and enhancing SAP SuccessFactors across a large, complex organisation. This role suits a seasoned functional analyst with strong module expertise, configuration capability and a passion for system improvement.

Key Responsibilities

Functional Support & Issue Resolution

Provide expert support across EC, Recruiting, Onboarding, Performance & Goals, Learning.
Resolve configuration, integration and data issues; manage escalations with SAP Support.

Configuration, Enhancements & Releases

Maintain and update system configurations and business rules.

Assess and support quarterly release impacts, regression testing and feature deployment.

Data Integrity & Management

Ensure consistent, high-quality data across modules and connected systems.

Support data loads, audits, mapping, validations and collaboration with HRIS/Payroll.

Reporting & Insights

Build and maintain reports and dashboards using Ad Hoc Reports, Report Center, Canvas.

Provide analytics support and guidance to HR and business teams.

Security & Access

Manage Role-Based Permissions (RBP), conduct audits and ensure compliance with security and privacy requirements.

Stakeholder Engagement & Change Support

Partner with HR, Payroll, IT and vendors to translate needs into system solutions.

Deliver user training, documentation and support change adoption.

Projects & Testing

Contribute to SIT/UAT, cutover, data validation and go-live activities.

Provide hypercare support and assist with continuous improvement initiatives.

About You

Strong functional experience across multiple SuccessFactors modules.

Hands-on configuration experience (EC, workflows, business rules, templates; provisioning desirable).

Solid understanding of HR processes and data structures.

Strong analytical, reporting and data validation skills.

Proven experience in testing, release management and supporting complex environments.

Excellent communication, problem solving and stakeholder engagement abilities.

About the company

Our client provides equipment and rental management software in a fully integrated ERP solution. Over the last 35 years, they have become the preferred true ERP software for companies that are serious about profit and evolving with technology. The fully integrated suite of modules includes Sales, Rentals, Service, Parts, and Financials plus helpful tools like CRM software.

From humble beginnings to becoming one of the world’s leading rental software companies is due to their tenacity to take on any challenge. Gaining business mainly through word of mouth and referral, they have grown their reputation for developing customised operations management software that manages the operations of businesses rather than just the invoicing.

About the role

The successful candidate will be responsible for end-to-end implementation and support of ERP solutions - design, business process review, system build, training, and post-implementation support.

The role can be based remotely, with interstate and overseas travel requirements 2-3 times per quarter.

Duties

Reporting to the Director of Customer Operations, the role is focussed on supporting and guiding clients through end to end implementations, which can typically take from 12- 18 months. You will be responsible for functional
specifications, system configuration, solution testing, and ensuring successful user experiences.

Acceptance testing, end-user training, and support
Business Process Review with prospects and customers
Requirements gathering and documentation with customers for modification development
Providing training to both customers and internal team members 
Perform data validation and reconciliation with the data conversion team and customers
Working with the Project Manager to deliver projects within scope, on time, and within budget 
Achieve productivity, customer satisfaction and billable KPI’s
Skills & Experience

The ideal candidate will have a track record of implementing ERP solutions from the vendor side or from a software consulting firm, with commercial experience and a strong business process understanding. 

Tertiary qualification in a business-related field (accounting/commerce) preferred
Strong knowledge of financials within ERP products 
Previous experience producing specifications for modifications for ERP systems
Client-facing ERP implementation experience
Experience with BI solutions such as Power BI, associated data analysis, SQL, and data warehousing
Culture

Their culture is supportive, inclusive and progressive. Many members of the team have been with the company for more than 10 years, which speaks volumes about the business. 
They always look to promote internally before taking any new roles to market which provides excellent career progression opportunities for their team. 

Benefits

On offer is a generous salary, performance bonuses, annual company bonus and long term career progression opportunities.

Ad Text:
Job Description

Digital Build Services is the innovation engine within KPMG Australia's Consulting division. Our focus is on transforming how we deliver solutions to clients and embed AI in the way we work. We are a highly motivated and collaborative multi-disciplinary team who combine deep business expertise with cutting-edge technology to design and build AI-first products that drive measurable impact for our people and our clients. 

Your Opportunity: 

Drive advanced analytics and AI initiatives that transform business challenges into innovative, data-driven solutions. This role focuses on evaluation-based design, applying AI and machine learning to deliver measurable impact while collaborating closely with stakeholders and supporting the analytics team.

Key Responsibilities:

Analytics & AI Expertise: Design and implement AI/ML models and analytics processes to solve complex business problems.

Evaluation-Based Design: Apply rigorous evaluation frameworks to ensure solutions meet accuracy, performance, and ethical standards.

Business Translation: Work with business leaders to translate strategic objectives into actionable analytics and AI workflows.

Collaboration & Guidance: Act as a senior resource within the team, providing technical insight and coaching to analysts when needed.

Innovation: Stay ahead of emerging trends in AI, machine learning, and analytics to keep the organisation at the forefront of industry practices.

Essential Skills & Qualifications

Advanced degree in AI, Machine Learning, Data Science, or related field.

Proven experience in developing and deploying AI/ML models for business applications.

Strong proficiency in Python for analytics and model development.

Excellent communication and interpersonal skills; able to influence and collaborate effectively.

Experience contributing to team development and supporting junior colleagues.

Desirable Attributes

Passion for innovation and solving complex problems.

Familiarity with ethical AI principles and evaluation methodologies.

Ability to integrate analytics into business strategy and operations.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

We’re looking for an experienced Systems Analyst / Business Analyst to join a major Finance Transformation Program.

This role is central to shaping and delivering future-state finance systems and processes, ensuring greater accuracy, automation, and streamlined reporting across the organisation.

You’ll work closely with a Project Manager, a Generalist BA, a Change Analyst, and Finance SMEs to help deliver an integrated and modernised finance environment.

As the Systems Analyst / Business Analyst, you’ll act as the crucial link between business needs and technical delivery. You will lead the analysis and documentation of finance system requirements, contribute to solution design and configuration, and support testing, data migration, and go-live readiness.

This role suits someone who enjoys working at the intersection of finance, technology, and process optimisation.

Key Responsibilities:
Analyse current finance processes and systems to identify improvement and automation opportunities.
Work with Finance SMEs to gather and document detailed business and system requirements.
Translate business needs into clear functional and technical specifications.
Partner with IT teams and external vendors on solution design, configuration, integration, and testing.
Support system testing, UAT, data migration, and deployment activities.
Work collaboratively with the Change Analyst to ensure users are prepared and supported through transition.
Maintain high-quality documentation and ensure alignment with finance governance and controls.
Skills & Experience:
5+ years as a Systems Analyst, Business Analyst, or Functional Consultant on finance or ERP transformation projects.
Strong understanding of core finance processes (Record-to-Report, Procure-to-Pay, Order-to-Cash).
Hands-on experience with major finance/ERP platforms (SAP, Oracle, Workday, D365, TechnologyOne, etc.).
Excellent analytical and problem-solving ability with strong attention to detail.
Confident communicator, able to work effectively with both finance stakeholders and technical teams.
Experience supporting testing, data migration, and implementation activities.
Desirable: Accounting background or CA/CPA, plus experience in process improvement or change initiatives.
Team Environment You’ll be joining a supportive and collaborative project team that includes:

Project Manager
Generalist Business Analyst
Change Analyst
Finance SMEs (Accounting, Reporting, Operations)
The team works closely with IT and external vendors to deliver a fully integrated finance solution.

You’ll thrive in this role if you are:

Technically capable yet business-focused, with a knack for translating finance needs into system solutions.
Comfortable working in a project environment with multiple concurrent workstreams.
Proactive, detail-oriented, and collaborative.

We’ve been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with over 115,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you’ll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you’ll also get to see your impact.

About the team

Strategy is making the future of retail a reality. We’re a big business with big ideas. Our team works together with all our business units to help bring those ideas to life. We stay focused on what’s next, so we can make our customers’ experiences even better now and lead the industry for years to come.

About the role

A permanent opportunity exists for a dynamic Strategy Business Partner (SBP) to join our Group Strategy function. In this pivotal role, you will partner with senior stakeholders to shape and execute Coles’ strategic priorities, ensuring we remain a world class retailer. You’ll play a critical role in turning insights into action, supporting decision making at the highest level, and driving initiatives that deliver long-term value. Your key responsibilities will include:

Deliver fact-based insights to inform business strategies, the corporate plan, and solutions to critical challenges. 
Partner with Strategy Managers and the Head of Group Strategy to design and execute Coles’ strategy. 
Apply structured problem solving and rigorous analysis to develop initiatives and define success metrics for strategic issues. 
Act as a strategic thought partner to senior stakeholders, driving execution of key initiatives. 
Conduct high quality quantitative and qualitative analysis to solve complex business problems. 
Synthesise findings into clear recommendations that enable effective execution. 
Take ownership of project success within your area of responsibility, ensuring timely and impactful delivery. 
Identify risks to in scope projects and support the development of mitigation plans. 

About you and your skills


You are a strategic thinker with strong analytical capabilities, able to turn complexity into clarity and influence senior stakeholders with confidence. You will bring

Previous experience in management consulting (ideally MBB), investment banking, or retail strategy. 
Proven expertise in complex analytical problem solving (e.g., hypothesis-based approaches). 
Advanced proficiency in financial modelling and tools such as PowerPoint and Excel. 
Experience managing work streams within large scale projects. 
Ability to craft and contribute to board-level presentations and reports. 
Strong communication and presentation skills with senior stakeholders. 
Experience collaborating across cross-functional business units. 
A track record of thriving in high performance team environments. 

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

Company: Australian Institute of Health and Welfare
Ad Text:
The Australian Institute of Health and Welfare (AIHW) is Australia’s authoritative source of health and welfare data and analysis. As an independent national information and statistics agency within the Commonwealth’s Health portfolio, the AIHW publishes more than 400 data products each year, maintains and administers specialised national data standards and classifications, and supports high quality research.

AIHW are seeking to fill two roles:

- Group Head – Population Health Group SES Band 1; and

- Group Head – Housing and Specialised Services Group, SES Band 1.

The AIHW has recently established 3 divisions - the Health Insights Division, Community and First Nations Insights Division and the Corporate Strategy and Performance Division. Currently, Group Head vacancies exist in the Health Insights Division (for the Population Health Group), and the Community and First Nations Insights Division (for the Housing and Specialised Services Group). Both these roles report to Executive Directors (SES Band 2) and form part of the institute’s senior leadership team.

The Population Health Group comprises several units covering burden of disease, cancer, chronic conditions, preventive health and injuries. The group collects, compiles, analyses and presents comprehensive data about the health of Australians. The group has a particular role to play in expanding the amount of evidence available, particularly in relation to cancer and linkage across domains such as aged care and disability.

The Housing and Specialised Services Group comprises several units that collect and analyse data to support reporting and policy decisions on the health and welfare of Australians. The Group has a particular focus on specialised services including housing, veterans supports, drug and alcohol supports, child protection systems, youth justice systems and correctional facilities.

To be a strong contender for either of these important roles you will have experience leading data management, analytical, reporting and/or statistical functions and have a strong working understanding of the Australian health and welfare landscape. You will excel in working in complex environments and you will be forward thinking, innovative and adept at building relationships across a broad range of sectors. Your integrity, judgement and strong leadership credentials will be paramount. Your impressive personal style and ability to engender trust and respect will be complemented by intellectual rigor, critical analysis, and first class communication and presentation skills.

For further information on the eligibility requirements, selection criteria and how to apply please visit the AIHW careers page and download the position description. If, after reading the selection documentation, you require further information please contact Tricia Searson or Karina Duffey at Executive Intelligence Group on (02) 6232 2200.

Applications close: 11.30pm AEDT 30 November 2025.

Company: Australian Institute of Health and Welfare
Ad Text:
The Australian Institute of Health and Welfare (AIHW) is Australia’s authoritative source of health and welfare data and analysis. As an independent national information and statistics agency within the Commonwealth’s Health portfolio, the AIHW publishes more than 400 data products each year, maintains and administers specialised national data standards and classifications, and supports high quality research.

AIHW are seeking to fill two roles:

- Group Head – Population Health Group SES Band 1; and

- Group Head – Housing and Specialised Services Group, SES Band 1.

The AIHW has recently established 3 divisions - the Health Insights Division, Community and First Nations Insights Division and the Corporate Strategy and Performance Division. Currently, Group Head vacancies exist in the Health Insights Division (for the Population Health Group), and the Community and First Nations Insights Division (for the Housing and Specialised Services Group). Both these roles report to Executive Directors (SES Band 2) and form part of the institute’s senior leadership team.

The Population Health Group comprises several units covering burden of disease, cancer, chronic conditions, preventive health and injuries. The group collects, compiles, analyses and presents comprehensive data about the health of Australians. The group has a particular role to play in expanding the amount of evidence available, particularly in relation to cancer and linkage across domains such as aged care and disability.

The Housing and Specialised Services Group comprises several units that collect and analyse data to support reporting and policy decisions on the health and welfare of Australians. The Group has a particular focus on specialised services including housing, veterans supports, drug and alcohol supports, child protection systems, youth justice systems and correctional facilities.  

To be a strong contender for either of these important roles you will have experience leading data management, analytical, reporting and/or statistical functions and have a strong working understanding of the Australian health and welfare landscape. You will excel in working in complex environments and you will be forward thinking, innovative and adept at building relationships across a broad range of sectors. Your integrity, judgement and strong leadership credentials will be paramount. Your impressive personal style and ability to engender trust and respect will be complemented by intellectual rigor, critical analysis, and first class communication and presentation skills.

For further information on the eligibility requirements, selection criteria and how to apply please visit the AIHW careers page and download the position description. If, after reading the selection documentation, you require further information please contact Tricia Searson or Karina Duffey at Executive Intelligence Group on (02) 6232 2200. 

Applications close: 11.30pm AEDT 30 November 2025.
